 with the `varhandle`. If it fails, does that mean the test fails too, leading to no coverage? I wonder if the initial resolve covers this, but it seems like the coverage might not include it when using `MethodHandles`. Also, could it be that the main path has a `SecurityManager` set to false? I'm not entirely sure, but it raises some interesting points to consider.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating agent records**\\n\\nI'm wondering about tracing agent records and how they interact with reflective Class.forName. Do they record the class in the reflective config even if loaded? Or is it different when it's just a class lookup without member access? I'm considering if a dynamic access report tracks API calls through custom JVM instrumentation, and whether it can observe native-image-agent output. There’s a lot here to think through!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4ruD95ChOWSEiFJ4H1rrEQk2|fc_09582281f12fb64f0169fb9e524be08197aba459b914695bc0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.thoughtworks.qdox/qdox/1.12.1/main/extracted/com/thoughtworks/qdox/model/annotation/EvaluatingVisitor.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 10481, "output": 2779, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36300, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778097702942, "responseId": "resp_09582281f12fb64f0169fb9e285c8081979e20d780300d6f58"}}
